Toronto, ON
Location: Toronto, ON, CA, M5G 1X6
Req ID: 8346
Status: Full Time, Regular
Education Level: Bachelor's Degree with a focus in Finance, Business, Economics, Math, Statistics, Engineering, Business Administration, and/or a relevant study is required.
Location: Downtown Toronto
Deadline to Apply: March 12, 2020
BE THE GENERATION to challenge and change.
At Ontario Power Generation (OPG), our values are our strengths. They are fundamental truths about us that don’t change. Safety. Integrity. Excellence. People and Citizenship. We operate a diverse portfolio of generation assets including nuclear, hydroelectric, biomass and solar, and offer challenging and unique work opportunities. BE THE GENERATION to power tomorrow.
JOB OVERVIEW
Ontario Power Generation (OPG) is looking for a dynamic, consultative and results-driven professional to join our team in the role of Investment Senior Analyst / Associate at our Downtown Toronto location.
Reporting to the Senior Manager, Strategic Initiatives, the Investment Senior Analyst / Associate’s primary role is to participate in teams developing and evaluating major corporate capital investments and strategic initiatives. The successful candidate will build and maintain complex financial models related to the economic evaluation of acquisition opportunities, capital investments, and strategic business decisions. In addition, the Investment Associate will be required to remain abreast of energy asset transactions occurring in the capital markets, and prepare data, market analysis and forecasts to evaluate the underlying investment thesis related to capital deployment opportunities.
This is an exciting opportunity to work in an environment where you will contribute to Ontario Power Generation’s continued growth and success in generating safe, clean, reliable low-cost power in a sustainable manner.
KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES
Build and maintain complex financial models related to the economic evaluation of energy assets, strategic initiatives and potential acquisition opportunities;
Take a leading role in the formulation of the business case / investment strategy supporting potential capital investments and M&A opportunities taking account of the technical, financial and business risks associated with the potential transaction;
Communicate the results of analysis, both orally and written, via presentations, memoranda, and reports. Explain complex financial and technical concepts clearly and concisely;
Participate in the identification and origination of potential capital investments and business development opportunities, in line with OPG’s growth objectives;
Monitor trends and valuations in the market for energy assets. Maintain a database of market transactions;
Monitor developments in electricity, energy and financial markets and incorporate changes and updates as appropriate in the models and databases on a timely basis;
Take a leading role in the detailed due diligence process related to any potential transactions. Coordinate with multi-disciplinary teams across the organization to ensure required outputs are received in a timely manor;
Monitor major generation projects in the planning and execution stages with focus on nuclear, combined cycle gas turbine and hydroelectric developments. Keep abreast of various procurement programs and announced projects by the Independent Electricity System Operator, Ontario government and others. Monitor and review government and industry publications and related studies on generation options, environmental technologies and policies;
Coordinate and assemble data and conduct analysis in support of reporting to external agencies (e.g., IESO, NPCC). Support working groups, committees and task forces with external agencies and industry groups on electricity planning, reliability studies, market structuring, financial evaluations and modeling, industry and environmental regulations and other related studies;
Provide support to senior staff involved in the negotiation of electricity contracts such as Power Purchase Agreements (PPA) or Energy Supply Agreements (ESA) with the Independent Electricity System Operator or Ontario government; and
Provide financial modelling expertise to assist other groups within OPG and perform other duties as required.
EDUCATION
Bachelor's Degree with a focus in Finance, Business, Economics, Math, Statistics, Engineering, Business Administration, and/or a relevant study is required; and
Masters of Business Administration (MBA), CPA / CA, CFA or CBV designation(s) would be an asset.
QUALIFICATIONS
Between 5-10 years of progressive experience; However, candidates with fewer years experience may be considered, particularly those with a minimum of 3 years of focused experience working on evaluating major capital projects and M&A transactions in the energy or infrastructure sectors. Financial advisory, project finance, or buy-side experience is highly desirable;
Experience creating complex financial models incorporating operational and capital structuring considerations to forecast returns and conduct detailed scenario analysis;
Extensive experience with the development and application of economic, financial and rate models in evaluation of major projects and contracts;
Experience in a similar type of consultative role that provided effective financial guidance to the business and department managers;
Strong written and verbal communication skills to prepare effective documentation, maintain contact and ability to influence and communicate effectively with all internal and external stakeholders at all levels, and ability to present investment materials to senior management;
Experience with the practical application of mathematical and quantitative risk concepts to the modeling and evaluation of investments, electric load, generation production and revenue, and strategic initiatives;
Knowledge of the structure of energy markets, engineering, power systems, generation assets, project management and commercial contracts would be an asset;
Experience performing quantitative risk assessment (i.e. Monte Carlo Simulations) would be an asset;
Excellent negotiation skills and demonstrated critical thinking skills;
Strong interpersonal skills, experience in maintaining productive relationships;
Ability to quickly understand business processes, corporate projects and strategic initiatives; and their risk implications in order to analyze these complex situations to reach appropriate conclusions and recommendations;
Strong sense of urgency and decision making skills conducive to managing priorities and meeting internal and external timelines;
High level of proficiency with the use of technology tools such as MS Office (Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint and Outlook) including advanced knowledge and experience working with MS Excel required;
A results-oriented focus is essential, as is the ability to work in a fast-paced changing environment and effectively manage several projects simultaneously; and
Experience and exposure working in/for energy or infrastructure investments, power generation or utilities is preferred.
The successful candidate will exhibit uncompromising integrity and commitment to upholding corporate values and the OPG Code of Business Conduct.
WHY OPG?
As Ontario’s largest clean energy generator, Ontario Power Generation offers an exciting combination of challenging opportunities and career diversity in a work environment. Being an OPG employee means you can apply your knowledge, broaden your skills and make a valuable contribution to an organization that is vital to Ontario's success. At OPG our values are our strengths. They are fundamental truths about our organization that don’t change. Safety. Integrity. Excellence. People and Citizenship.
Here's why OPG might just be the ideal workplace for you:
Exceptional range of opportunities
Long-term career growth and development opportunities
Electricity is vital to our future
If you are looking to learn from others and be part of something important, and you are excited about the future of power generation, you will find the right fit at OPG.
Our promise to you
We care about the safety and the well-being of our employees. It is our utmost priority.
A supportive work environment where you can be your best every day.
Opportunities to stretch and develop in our diverse lines of business.
Provide spaces for innovative thinking and solutions, such as Launchpad or X-Lab.
Offer different ways for you to give back to communities where we operate.
We support employment equity and diversity.
APPLICATION PROCESS
Please submit your application online at https://jobs.opg.com/ by 11:59 PM E.S.T., March 12, 2020. OPG thanks all those who apply; however, only candidates considered for an interview will be contacted.
ACCOMMODATIONS
OPG is committed to fostering an inclusive, equitable, and accessible environment where all employees feel valued, respected, and supported. If you require accommodation during the application or interview process, please advise us as soon as possible so appropriate arrangements can be made.
If you require technical support in a format that is accessible to you, please contact AODA@opg.com
.
